Better Than Expected Performance Across SegmentsBaozun reported 2Q results with revenue beat and non- GAAP op profit (excludes one- off expense) ahead of expectations. Management highlighted solid performance in 618 and continues to empower brand partners in driving growth with digitalization tools. Fundamentals of BEC continue to improve, excluding one- off impact. For BBM, we expect Gap to achieve breakeven in 4Q. We raise full year revenue estimates reflecting better BBM performance. Maintain Buy.

2Q25 results highlights. Total revenue increased \(6.8\%\) YoY to RMB2.55bn, \(3.6\%\) and \(3.7\%\) above consensus and our estimate. By segment, service revenue increased \(2.5\%\) YoY to RMB1.6bn (vs with our estimate at RMB1.48bn), and product sales revenue increased by \(14.2\%\) YoY to RMB994m (vs our estimate at RMB986.9m). Gross profit reached RMB1.84bn (vs our estimate at RMB1.8bn) and GPM was \(72.1\%\) (vs our estimate at \(73.2\%\) ). Non- GAAP operating profit reached RMB6.1m vs our estimate of RMB43.4m, with adjusted operating profit for ecommerce at RMB41.1m and brand management operating loss at (RMB35m). Non- GAAP net loss reached (RMB18m) vs consensus at RMB34.4m and our estimate of RMB26.6m.

Key takeaways from the conference call. These include: BEC. (1) During 618, GMV from Tmall and JD both had growth; Tmall GMV growth is 2- 3x compared with JD; (2) Co highlighted that it has a lot of categories, and its FMCG sector is testing the water in instant retail, and it will keep tracking in the long run; (3) Ecommerce platforms prioritize traffic allocation over absolute low price. Tmall and JD are trying to re allocate high- quality traffic to brands to prevent rat racing on price in long run; (4) Thanks to the strong 618 shopping festival, co highlighted it foresees strong Double 11 in 4Q and promising 2H25; (5) BZUN is on the list as top selection of the program with XHS, so co will have exposure to all the brands with early initiative; (6) For Double 11 this year, co mentioned a lot of brand partners and confident leveraging expertise and experience in 618 festival, and more brands are planning on adding more inventory and budget for Double 11; (7) BZUN conducted a thorough review of its partnership scope and terms, which help align with partners' evolving needs; (8) BEC products sales growth in the quarter was driven by strong performance in beauty and cosmetics categories and also achieved consistent breakthrough, a alcohol and apparel categories. BBM (1) Co will continue to expand stores offline, expanding products and launch activities both online and offline; (2) BZUN has confidence to achieve full- year business objective and achieve GAP breakeven in 4Q25;

We see Baozun as a critical ecommerce service provider, adding value via three different units - ecommerce, logistics, and technology - the last empowers brands to improve efficiency, with a complete suite of resources such as cloud, digital tools, and warehousing systems. Non- GAAP operating margin expansion is mainly due to scalability. We expect Baozun to continue to shift from a distribution business model to a non- distribution model, with the latter monetizing brands through service fees and the consignment model.
Risk/Reward - 12 Month View

In 2019, Baozun strengthened its corporate structure and divided its business into three segments: ecommerce, logistics, and technology; the last is crucial in empowering brands to improve efficiency, with a complete suite of resources such as cloud, digital tools, and warehousing systems. We expect Baozun to enjoy rapid growth, backed by consumption upgrade and solid execution. PT at US\$4.5 (HK\$10.9) based on PE valuation.
Stronger- than- expected GMV growth. Stronger- than- expected margin expansion due to leverage in sales and marketing, and fulfillment expense. PT at US\$6.75 (HK\$16.35) based on PE valuation.

New entrants to the industry with superior technological expertise and fulfillment capabilities. Material slowdown in online shopping due to macro headwinds. Brands pursue omni- channel strategies with in- house resources. PT at US\$2.25 (HK\$5.45) based on PE valuation.

Top Material Issue(s): 1) Customer Privacy / Data Security: BZUN has accumulated a large amount of data, containing names, telephone numbers, addresses and other customer information during operation, and data leakage will not only cause economic losses, but also bring negative impact to consumers. 2) Employee Engagement, Diversity & Inclusion: A large and diverse company as BZUN must pay attention to the equality and development of employees and create an inclusive work environment for employees, and protect their rights and interests as well.
Company Target(s): 1) Reduce carbon emission (Scope I, II, III) by 50% by 2030 against base year FY2022. Achieve carbon neutrality across the value chain (including Scopes I, II and III) by 2050.

Qs. Target: 1) What measures have been taken to protect consumers' personal data? 2) What types of technologies are still required for development to better serve clients and consumers? 3) What cost- savings do you expect from green office initiation?
Further partnerships with Tmall. Stronger- than- expected GMV growth. Faster- than- expected margin expansion from operating leverage.

(3) BZUN has a brand portfolio strategy and will have multiple brands. Management highlights it has a large client base and can cultivate some brands from ecommerce collaboration to brand management, and these brands should be energetic and have great potential online and offline as well as bringing growth and profit; (4) BZUN has reduced partial agreement with a Yoga brand, and co considers it good timing as this new brand can benefit from the two existing brands, such as in designing, supply chain capabilities as well as operational capabilities; (5) BZUN expanded with 11 new openings in the quarter and reaching a total of 156 locations, and it emphasizes leveraging an asset-light approach and targeting for 40 new stores for full year 2025; (6) Inventory management was a standout with days of inventory reduced to 126 days representing a more than 20% year- over-year improvement; (7) Co opened 3 Hunter flagship stores and will continue to diversify product matrix with new line introduction, innovation and customer satisfaction. Al. (1) BZUN spent significant resources to increase efficiency and develop internal tools; (2) Co highlighted that Al is not leveraged to generate revenue but rather to drive efficiency.

Valuation and risks. We reiterate our Buy rating and PT post results. Key risks include: (1) entry of new firms with better technological expertise and fulfillment capabilities; (2) material slowdown in online shopping due to macro headwinds; and (3) brands pursuing omni- channel strategies on their own, leveraging in- house resources.

Baozun Baozun Inc. provides ecommerce solutions. The company's services include website design, development and hosting, information technology infrastructure, customer service, warehousing, and logistics services, as well as digital marketing. Baozun serves customers in China.

We have a Buy rating and PT of USD4.5/HKD10.9 based on \(7.7xP / E\) of organic business. Key risks include: (1) entry of new firms with better technological expertise and fulfillment capabilities; (2) material slowdown in online shopping due to macro headwinds; and (3) brands pursuing omni- channel strategies on their own, leveraging in- house resources.

We have a Buy rating and PT of US \(60 / HK\) 233 based on 9.2x 2025P/E (ex- new business). Key risks include (1) macro headwinds affecting GMV growth, especially in the electronics category; (2) intensified competition leading to margin pressure from aggressive marketing spending in the grocery category; and (3) user base growth in lower- tier cities falling below expectations on poor execution.

Buy - Describes securities that we expect to provide a total return (price appreciation plus yield) of \(15\%\) or more within a 12- month period. Hold - Describes securities that we expect to provide a total return (price appreciation plus yield) of plus \(15\%\) or minus \(10\%\) within a 12- month period. Underperform - Describes securities that we expect to provide a total return (price appreciation plus yield) of minus \(10\%\) or less within a 12- month period. The expected total return (price appreciation plus yield) for Buy rated securities with an average security price consistently below \(10\) is \(20\%\) or more within a 12- month period as these companies are typically more volatile than the overall stock market. For Hold rated securities with an average security price consistently below \(10\) , the expected total return (price appreciation plus yield) is plus or minus \(20\%\) within a 12- month period. For Underperform rated securities with an average security price consistently below \(10\) , the expected total return (price appreciation plus yield) is minus \(20\%\) or less within a 12- month period.

Jefferies Franchise Picks will include only Buy rated stocks and the number can vary depending on analyst recommendations for inclusion.
